First Non-Repeating Character in a String (Python)
ğŸ“Œ Problem Statement

Given a string consisting of lowercase English letters, find the first non-repeating character in the string.
If no such character exists, return $.

ğŸ§  Approach

Count the frequency of each character in the string.

Traverse the string again to find the first character with frequency 1.

If none is found, return $.

â±ï¸ Complexity Analysis

Time Complexity: O(n)

Space Complexity: O(1) (only 26 lowercase letters)
